[Hard Rules]

## Filing Rules
| Signal about... | File to | Slug format |
|---|---|---|
| Person | `people/` | `firstname-lastname` |
| Company / org | `companies/` | `company-name` |
| Active workstream | `projects/` | `project-name` |
| Scheduled event | `meetings/` | `YYYY-MM-DD-meeting-name` |
| Pre-execution concept | `ideas/` | `idea-name` |
| Recurring observation (3+) | `patterns/` | `pattern-name` |
| One-off learning | `insights/` | `insight-name` |
| Committed choice | `decisions/` | `YYYY-MM-DD-decision-name` |

## Anti-Patterns (NEVER do these)
- ❌ Raw meeting dump → meetings/. Extract entities first, file meeting as event, people as people/
- ❌ Duplicate entities. Always search entities.jsonl + aliases.jsonl before creating
- ❌ Filing a person under companies/ because they represent a company
- ❌ Filing an idea under projects/ before it has deliverables + timeline
- ❌ Creating two pages for same entity with different slugs
- ❌ Skipping alias registration — every known name variant must be in aliases.jsonl

## Dedup Protocol
1. Normalize name: lowercase, strip honorifics, expand abbreviations
2. Search entities.jsonl by normalized name
3. Search aliases.jsonl for known variants
4. If match found → return existing slug, do NOT create new
5. If no match → create entity + register all known aliases
